<subSubSection id="D8C2DEEDC758C75992D96BE8E0611441" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="05EFDD234A8C13A2ECC2B9B427EEA6A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D82AFC394247499F19E6B699966822F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.6 mm long (n = 1); 2.6
<normalizedToken id="302F025E0AB943B655437A335048FF45" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the discal interstriae confused; posterior margin of elytra broadly rounded; declivital face with interstriae 1 and 2 granulate, unarmed by tubercles; declivital face weakly sulcate; large body size; lateral declivital margins elevated, bearing five pairs of moderate, narrow, sharply pointed spines of equal size; sulcate area of declivity shagreened, dull; and stout body.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
